<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,152,391]" box="[199,1396,259,286]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,452,259,286]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Differential remarks.</emphasis>
This species is sympatric with 
<taxonomicName box="[803,970,260,286]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Microplinthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipennis">
<emphasis box="[803,970,260,286]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">M. brevipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species that has shortly oval elytra.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,152,391]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,434,293,320]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Origin of the name.</emphasis>
This species name derives from the main distinctive character of the species, the narrow and slender elytra.
</paragraph>
